<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The international thriller ``Black Rain'' was
No. 1 in national box office receipts for the second-straight
weekend, and two movies starring Ellen Barkin finished in the top
five.
   ``Black Rain,'' starring Michael Douglas as a policeman tracking
a Japanese fugitive, grossed $6.5 million last weekend.
   ``Sea of Love,'' featuring Al Pacino and Miss Barkin, was second
with $6.2 million.
   In third with $2.7 million was the comedy ``Uncle Buck,'' with
John Candy as an obnoxious relative asked to babysit for his nephew
and two nieces.
