<HEAD>Former Professor Leaves $1.2 Million for Scholarships</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VALDOSTA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A professor known for her frugal lifestyle
and concern for students has left Valdosta State College $1.2
million for scholarships.
   College President Hugh Bailey said the school received the money
recently from the estate of Gertrude Odum, who died Feb. 26, 1988,
at age 89.
   ``She lived in a very small house and lived very frugally,''
said Bailey. ``I think there's no question she desired to save her
money and help the students she loved so much.''
   Her husband, attorney John Odum, died several years earlier.
   A native of Shenandoah, Iowa, Mrs. Odum joined the faculty in
1921, rose to head the English Department and became a professor
emeritus in 1965.
