<FIRST>r a PM-People-ZsaZsaSuit     10-03 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Zsa Zsa Suit,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Zsa Zsa Not Court Shy After Conviction, Sues Neighbor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Zsa Zsa Gabor, convicted last week for
slapping a police officer, has filed suit against a neighbor,
claiming roots from his trees cracked her driveway.
   The Hungarian-born actress filed the lawsuit Monday in the Los
Angeles County Superior Court.
   She said she was forced to remove dried and overgrown brush
extending from the yard of Austin Young onto her property and to
install sprinklers and new plants at her own expense after Young
failed to clear the property.
   The lawsuit seeks at least $47,000 in damages and a court order
requiring Young to better maintain his yard.
   Young wrote in a June 1988 letter to Miss Gabor that he was
willing to arrange and pay for the driveway's repaving, but
couldn't reach her by telephone to discuss the work.
   On Friday, a Beverly Hills Municipal Court jury convicted Miss
Gabor of misdemeanor battery on an officer, driving with an expired
license and with an open container of alcohol in her Rolls Royce
Corniche.
   The charges stem from a traffic stop in which the actress
slapped Officer Paul Kramer.
   She could be sentenced to 18 months in jail. Sentencing is
scheduled for Oct. 17.
</TEXT>
