<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-03 0465</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0476</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snow in Idaho; Frost in Minnesota; Record Heat in Miami</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Four inches of snow covered parts of the northern Rockies early
today and Minneapolis got its first frost of the year.
   Light snow fell across parts of Idaho late Monday, coating the
Island Park area and the mountains on the Montana border. Gusty
north winds were sweeping the central mountains of Idaho this
morning, with sharply reduced visibility in some areas and up to 4
inches of snow.
   A snow advisory was in effect early today for the southern
mountains and passes of Montana where 2 to 6 inches were possible
at elevations above 5,000 feet.
   High winds buffeted parts of Nevada and Arizona, with gusts
reaching 43 mph at Kingman, Ariz.
   Temperatures dipped below freezing in southeastern Nebraska and
the Minneapolis-St. Paul area, the only part of Minnesota that had
yet to get frost.
   In Miami, meanwhile, temperatures soared to 94 on Sunday,
topping a nine-year-old record high for the date, and Waco, Texas
had a record 101 degrees.
   Showers and thunderstorms were scattered across southern Florida
on Monday evening, with rain extending from coastal North Carolina
to New England. Rain also fell in eastern Ohio, and from northern
California to western Wyoming.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 65 foggy; Atlanta 65 fair; Buffalo 50
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 72 fair; Chattanooga 63 foggy; Cincinnati
56 cloudy; Cleveland 56 showery; Detroit 48 partly cloudy; Hatteras
71 fair; Jacksonville 69 fair; Key West 83 partly cloudy; Knoxville
62 foggy; Macon 64 fair; Miami 80 fair; New York 65 foggy;
Philadelphia 65 foggy; Pittsburgh 61 cloudy; Portland, Maine 59
drizzle; Richmond 66 foggy; Tampa 72 fair; Washington, D.C. 65 fair.
   _Central: Birmingham 62 foggy; Bismarck 26 fair; Chicago 47
fair; Denver 47 fair; Des Moines 42 fair; Fort Worth 72 fair;
Indianapolis 58 fair; Kansas City 46 fair; Little Rock 66 fair;
Louisville 56 fair; Memphis 68 fair; Nashville 63 fair; New Orleans
67 foggy; North Platte 37 fair; Oklahoma City 58 fair; Omaha 45
partly cloudy; Rapid City 37 cloudy; St. Louis 52 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 31 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 37 partly cloudy;
San Antonio 75 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 71 partly cloudy; Anchorage 48 cloudy; Boise
46 rain; Casper 37 cloudy; Fairbanks 38 fair; Great Falls 36
cloudy; Honolulu 80 fair; Las Vegas 71 windy; Los Angeles 64
cloudy; Medford 54 fair; Pendleton 43 fair; Phoenix 84 fair;
Portland, Ore. 52 fair; Reno 44 showery; Salt Lake City 53 fair;
San Diego 66 cloudy; San Francisco 54 fair; Seattle 57 fair;
Spokane 43 fair.
   _International: Calgary 32 fair; Montreal 64 foggy; Ottawa 57
