<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A free-lance cameraman was summoned to meet with
CBS executives today to answer charges he faked Afghan combat
footage aired on Dan Rather's ``CBS Evening News,'' according to a
published report.
   The New York Post today quoted an unidentified source as saying
Mike Hoover flew to New York from New Zealand for the interview and
would be accompanied by an attorney at the meeting.
   A CBS News spokeswoman today declined to say if the Hoover was
meeting with executives of the news division. David Burke, CBS News
president, was out of his office and not available for comment, his
