   The Post reported last week that footage broadcast by CBS in
1984 was fake _ that Hoover had staged scenes of guerrilla sabotage
and had made a Pakistani jet fighter on a training run appear to be
a Soviet plane bombing Afghan villages.
   As a free-lancer, Hoover sold the film to CBS.
   CBS News president David Burke said last week, ``It is the goal
of CBS News in every instance to gather and report the news
accurately, fairly and with integrity. In the case of the Afghan
war, we believe we have done so.''
