<HEAD>Nine More Deputies Suspended In Money Skimming Probe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine sheriff's deputies were suspended
Tuesday in a probe into allegations of money skimming in the
department's narcotics bureau, officials said.
   A total of 18 deputies have now been suspended. Nine deputies
attached to the narcotics bureau were suspended five weeks ago in
connection with the investigation called ``Operation Big Spender.''
   Investigators say thousands of dollars seized in narcotics raids
may have been stolen.
   Twenty search warrants were also served, said Deputy Chris Wahla
of the Sheriff's Information Bureau. Among the homes searched were
those of the nine deputies suspended Tuesday, one retired deputy
and one police officer from another agency, Wahla said.
   Authorities refused to release the names of the deputies or the
department employing the one police officer whose home was searched.
