<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Coast Guard said it
confiscated 2,480 pounds of cocaine from a freighter and arrested
the crew of six Colombians and four Peruvians.
   In a statement released late Monday, the Coast Guard said the
freighter Argovind was seized off the coast of the Dutch island of
Saba in the eastern Caribbean early Sunday and brought to the Coast
Guard base in San Juan.
   U.S. Customs agents discovered the drugs Monday in a shipping
container, the release said.
   The Colombian and Peruvian crewmen, who were not identified by
the Coast Guard, were turned over to the Immigration and
Naturalization Service. The cocaine, for which no value was given,
was turned over to the Drug Enforcement Agency, the release said.
   The release did not mention the ship's registry or origin. Coast
Guard public affairs officials in San Juan could not be reached for
comment Tuesday.
