   Zenith Electronics Corp. said it will sell its
fast-growing computer business to France's Groupe Bull and use the
proceeds to pay off debt and sharpen its focus on new video
technology such as high-definition television.
   Zenith is the last major U.S.-based maker of televisions, a
business that generally has been unprofitable in recent years.
Company officials and industry analysts said Monday the deal,
valued at more than $630 million, would give Zenith a solid
financial base for its continuing battle against foreign
competitors.
