   Texas Oil &amp; Gas has been a disappointment to USX since it was
acquired in 1986 in a $3 billion stock swap.
   Analysts valued the reserves at around $1.5 billion. A sale is
anticipated by year's end, said USX spokesman William E. Keslar,
who declined to say Monday how USX values the reserves.
