<FIRST>r f PM-Zenith-Workers     10-03 0302</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Zenith-Workers,0315</SECOND>
<HEAD>Zenith's Sale of Computer Division Surprises Workers</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Zenith, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. JOSEPH, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 2,000 employees at Zenith
Electronic Corp.'s successful computer-manufacturing division
weren't surprised when they heard part of the company was being
sold.
   But they were shocked to learn Monday that the division being
sold was their own.
   ``I was surprised because the computer group of Zenith was the
one making the profits for the corporation itself. The other
divisions weren't,'' said Theodore J. Lesauskis, staff
representative for Local 8850 of the United Steelworkers.
   Zenith, based in Glenview, Ill., said it was selling its
personal computer division to Groupe Bull of France to reduce its
debt and focus on new video technologies.
   Groupe Bull said in a statement it planned to keep the Zenith
computer division's headquarters in the United States, with primary
manufacturing and engineering remaining in St. Joseph.
   ``As far as we're concerned, it's business as usual,'' Zenith
spokesman Matt Mirapaul said. ``We expect no major changes.''
   Lesauskis said Zenith officials told him Groupe Bull would pick
up the local's three-year contract, negotiated in July.
   There are about 750 union employees at the plant. About 150 were
laid off last month due to inventory surpluses, but Lesauskis
believes they will be called back if Zenith wins a military
contract on which it is bidding.
   ``The people (employees) are taking a wait-and-see attitude,''
Lesauskis said of the sale, which is subject to shareholder and
regulatory approval.
   ``It might be good. This French company has markets overseas
that might be helpful for the employees and company itself to
expand.''
   Zenith Data Systems is one of the world's leading producers of
laptop computers. It also has a large line of full-size personal
computers. The computer and components portion of the business also
includes the Heath Co.
</TEXT>
