<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Daniel P. Kearney, a Boston mortgage finance
specialist, was named president and chief executive officer of the
Resolution Trust Corp. Oversight Board, Treasury Secretary Nicholas
F. Brady announced Tuesday.
   The board is the Cabinet-level, policy-making body created by
Congress to manage the cleanup of the insolvent savings and loan
institutions. Brady is the board chairman.
   Kearney succeeds Deputy Treasury Secretary John E. Robson, who
has been serving as acting president since the board was
established Aug. 9.
   Kearney is a principal at Aldrich, Eastman &amp; Waltch, Inc., a
Boston pension fund adviser. Prior to joining AEW in 1988, he was a
managing director at Salomon Brothers Inc., in charge of the Real
Estate Financing Department and one of the founders of the firm's
Mortgage Securities Department.
