   Prices advanced on Wall Street today as
investors grew more optimistic about the outlook for interest rates
and scooped up blue chip issues.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials surged 24.31 to 2,738.03
as of 3 p.m. EDT after climbing nearly 21 points on Monday.
   The broader market also gained, although it lagged somewhat
behind the blue chips. Advancers outnumbered losers by a margin of
about 11 to 7 in nationwide trading of New York Stock
Exchange-listed issues, with 875 stocks up, 569 down and 506
unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 147.45 million shares with one
hour of trading left.
   The market gathered some forward momentum late Monday in a late
round of buying that lifted the Dow Jones industrial average above
2,700 to a four-week high and that continued into today.
   Analysts said a stronger dollar and gains on the bond markets
helped spark today's Wall Street advance.
   Bond prices moved higher on optimism that interest rates might
come down. Prices of long-term Treasury bonds rose about $3 for
each $1,000 in face value, lowering their yields to about 8.18
percent.
   Analysts said hopes seemed to be increasing that the Federal
Reserve might soon find room to relax its credit policy further,
given a relatively slow pace of economic growth and no recent sign
of increasing inflationary pressures.
   The Fed's policy-making body, the Federal Open Market Committee,
was meeting today, but it was unlikely that the central bank would
immediately announce any decisions.
   The most actively-traded issue on the NYSE was USX, which rose {
to 35]. On Monday, the company announced it was selling oil and
natural gas reserves through its Texas Oil &amp; Gas Corp. subsidiary,
and analysts have estimated USX could get $1.5 billion in the sale.
   Among other blue chip issues, Boeing was up 2] to 59 as the
company's unionized machinists voted on whether to accept a
three-year contract offer or reaffirm a midnight strike deadline.
   IBM was off 2~ to 105}, American Express was up 2 to 38 and
General Electric rose \ to 58.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
gained 1.18 to 196.08. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index was up 2.45 at 392.11.
