<HEAD>Saab Manager Excludes Takeover By Ford</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANTWERP, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The manager of the Swedish automobile
company Saab Scania said Tuesday there was no question of a
takeover by Ford Motor Co.
   Kai Hammerich, who was meeting with the press at the Saab plant
in Bornem near Antwerp, said his company was having talks with the
U.S. carmaker on a possible cooperation or association but he
denied any plan for a takeover or merger.
   Saab lost $120 million in the first half of this year,
essentially due to lower U.S. sales, and plans to lay off 2,000 of
its 14,000 workers, the company has announced previously.
